        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 16 at 9:26PM CDT by NWS Dodge City KS</headline>
        <description>At 926 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near St. John to near Windhorst. Movement was
east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
St. John, Belpre, Macksville, Dillwyn, Lewis, and Offerle around
930 PM CDT.
Kinsley and Stafford around 935 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
